# Component usage docs — keep in sync

When you **add, change, or remove** anything in a component under `src/lib/components/`, update the matching usage document so the docs stay accurate.

## Mapping

| Component file | Usage doc |
|----------------|-----------|
| `button/Button.svelte` | `docs/components/Button.md` |
| `accordion/Accordion.svelte` | `docs/components/Accordion.md` |
| `accordion-item/AccordionItem.svelte` | `docs/components/AccordionItem.md` |
| `input/Input.svelte` | `docs/components/Input.md` |
| `textarea/Textarea.svelte` | `docs/components/Textarea.md` |
| `form-select/FormSelect.svelte` | `docs/components/FormSelect.md` |

**Rule:** For any `*.svelte` in `src/lib/components/`, the doc is `docs/components/<Name>.md` where `<Name>` is the PascalCase component name (e.g. `accordion-item/AccordionItem.svelte` → `AccordionItem.md`).

## What to update in the doc

- **Props/attributes** — Add, remove, or change type/default/description.
- **Slots** — Add, remove, or rename slots and describe content.
- **Events** — Document new events or change names/details.
- **CSS variables** — List any new or removed design tokens the component uses.
- **Examples** — Adjust or add examples so they match the current API and behavior.

## New components

When you add a **new** component (e.g. `src/lib/components/card/Card.svelte`):

1. Create `docs/components/Card.md` with the same structure as existing docs (Overview, Custom element tag, Props, Slots, Events, CSS variables, Examples).
2. Add an entry for it in `docs/README.md` and, if needed, in this rule’s mapping table.

Each usage doc starts with a “Keep in sync” note that points to the source `.svelte` file; use that as the single source of truth when editing the doc.
